environment.model.roadusers.vehicles

Class TestVehicle

  • java.lang.Object
    • environment.model.roadusers.vehicles.TestVehicle
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    TestFamilySedan_Vehicle, TestMotorbike_Vehicle, TestSmallCar_Vehicle, TestTruck_Vehicle

    public abstract class TestVehicle
extends java.lang.Object
    Test the Vehicle class for expected behaviour.

    All tests should pass, and the tests are designed to check if the Vehicle objects have the correct attributes and that the methods modify the state of the Vehicle correctly or return correct values.

    This class must be extended by a test class for each Vehicle.

    Since:
    04/04/2017
    Version:
    12/04/2017
    Author:

      • testSize

        public final void testSize()
        Test the Vehicle.size field.

        It is expected that the Vehicle has a static field called "UNIT_SIZE" which contains the Vehicle.size of that Vehicle type, which all instances of that Vehicle must have the same Vehicle.size.

        See Also:
        Vehicle.size

      • testTankSize

        public final void testTankSize()
        Test the Vehicle.tankSize field of the Vehicle class.

        The Vehicle class should have either:

        • A MIN_TANK_SIZE and a TANK_SIZE_RANGE constant
        • A TANK_SIZE constant

        All Vehicle objects must be in the range of Min_TANK_SIZE and MIN_TANK_SIZE + TANK_SIZE_RANGE - 1, or have the exact Vehicle.tankSize of TANK_SIZE.

        See Also:
        Vehicle.tankSize

      • testFillAndIsFull

        public final void testFillAndIsFull()

        Test Vehicle.fill() and Vehicle.isFull() by:

        1. Checking if all Vehicle object are not full upon creation
        2. Check if filling the Vehicle objects Vehicle.tankSize - 1 results in the Vehicle still being not full
        3. Check if all Vehicle objects are full after filling them one more time
        4. Check if further filling the Vehicle objects will change the result of the Vehicle.isFull() method

        See Also:
        Vehicle.fill(), Vehicle.isFull()

      • testGetCurrentWorthAndGetMaxWorth

        public final void testGetCurrentWorthAndGetMaxWorth()
        Test the Vehicle.getCurrentWorth() and Vehicle.getMaxWorth() method.

        When a Vehicle is created, the current worth will always be 0.0. When the Vehicle.fill() method is used, the current worth of the car will increase (unless the car is already) full. When a Vehicle is full, the current worth should equal the max worth.

        See Also:
        Vehicle.getCurrentWorth(), Vehicle.getMaxWorth()

      • testClone

        public final void testClone()
        Test the Vehicle.clone() method from the Vehicle class.

        The created clones must:

        2. Be equal to the original object
        3. Not change the state of the original object
        4. Have the same state as the original object

        See Also:
        Vehicle.clone()

      • testEquals

        public final void testEquals()
        Test the Vehicle.equals(Object) method.

        Check if two Vehicle objects will be equal if:

        1. They have identical Vehicle.size
        2. They have identical Vehicle.tankSize
        3. They have a matching FuelType

        See Also:
        Vehicle.equals(Object)
